<li>Now a nation's character is in its literature.</li>
<li>He was an enthusiast—enthusiasm is needed for action; calculation never acts—it is a passive principle.</li>
<li>Why, the very element of poetry is faith—faith in the beautiful, the divine, and the true.</li>
